      • get

        public java.util.Optional<?> get(java.lang.String fieldName)
        Access a field value by name - inefficient

        This is inefficient. It is much more efficient to access it by index. The critical processing path should bake the indexes that need setting into the code, rather than setting by name. See KsqlStruct.get(int).

        Parameters:
        fieldName - the name of the field to access.
        Returns:
        the value of the field.
